---
/**
 * @file apps/web/src/pages/transparency.astro
 * @author Guy Romelle Magayano
 * @description Transparency page explaining how the site operates, what it is for, and the boundaries behind it.
 */

import Container from "@web/components/Container.astro";
import PageIntro from "@web/components/PageIntro.astro";
import { profile } from "@web/data/site";
import BaseLayout from "@web/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import {
  buildPortfolioPageMetadata,
  getPortfolioBrochurePage,
  getPortfolioSocialLinkByPlatform,
} from "@web/lib/portfolio-brochure";

const { page } = await getPortfolioBrochurePage("transparency");
const metadata = buildPortfolioPageMetadata(page);
const emailLink = getPortfolioSocialLinkByPlatform("email");
---

<BaseLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <PageIntro
    subheading={page.subheading}
    title={page.title}
    intro={page.intro}
  />

  <section aria-labelledby="transparency-content-heading" role="region">
    <Container class="py-16">
      <h2 id="transparency-content-heading" class="sr-only">
        Transparency details
      </h2>
      <div class="prose max-w-3xl prose-zinc dark:prose-invert">
        <h2>Why this page exists</h2>
        <p>
          I would rather say these things plainly than leave them to guesswork.
          If you are here as a client, recruiter, collaborator, or a curious
          visitor, I want you to understand what this site is for, what kind of
          professional intent sits behind it, and what boundaries matter to me.
        </p>
        <p>
          I do not think trust should depend on reading between the lines. This
          page exists so the site can speak more directly about that.
        </p>

        <h2>What this site is for</h2>
        <p>
          This site is the public home for {profile.name}'s work, writing,
          experiments, and professional direction. It is where I try to make my
          work legible: how I think, what I build, what I care about, and what
          kind of problems I want to be trusted with.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is also meant to help people decide whether there is a real fit for
          a conversation, collaboration, or opportunity without needing to
          decode a polished version of me first.
        </p>

        <h2>How this work is sustained</h2>
        <p>
          This site supports my professional work. That can include consulting,
          advisory conversations, full-time opportunities, collaborations, or
          other kinds of serious technical work. I do not want that intent to be
          hidden.
        </p>
        <p>
          At the same time, I do not want every page to read like an intake
          form. The point is not to turn attention into a funnel. The point is
          to present my work honestly enough that the right conversations can
          happen for the right reasons.
        </p>

        <h2>Recommendations and incentives</h2>
        <p>
          If I recommend a tool, pattern, team, or way of working here, I want
          that recommendation to be read as genuine judgment first, not as a
          disguised sales layer.
        </p>
        <p>
          There are no affiliate links, paid placements, or sponsored
          recommendations on this site today. If that changes in a meaningful
          way, I would rather label it plainly where it matters than hide it in
          tone, momentum, or fine print.
        </p>

        <h2>Information and boundaries</h2>
        <p>
          Like most websites, this one can receive limited technical and
          communication information needed to operate, understand usage at a
          high level, and respond clearly when someone reaches out. I do not
          want data collection to become the point of the site.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>I do not sell visitor information.</li>
          <li>I do not run this site as an advertising machine.</li>
          <li>
            I do not use hidden sponsorships or disguised paid recommendations.
          </li>
          <li>
            I do not treat direct contact as permission for unrelated follow-up.
          </li>
          <li>
            I do not want to collect more information than is useful for running
            the site and responding well.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Contact and next steps</h2>
        <p>
          If you contact me, I treat that as the start of a direct conversation,
          not as consent for broad marketing or unrelated outreach.
        </p>
        <p>
          If I need context to respond well, I may keep only what is useful for
          that exchange. What I do not want is for a simple inquiry to quietly
          turn into something broader than the person intended.
        </p>
        <p>
          If future scheduling, payment, or formal engagement steps need to
          happen, I would rather handle those through a separate page or flow
          built for that purpose. A casual message should stay a casual message
          until both sides are clearly choosing something more formal.
        </p>
        <p>
          If anything here feels unclear, questions about this page can be sent
          through the contact page
          {
            emailLink ? (
              <>
                {" "}
                or by emailing <a href={emailLink.href}>{profile.name}</a>
              </>
            ) : null
          }
          .
        </p>

        <h2>Living note</h2>
        <p>
          This page is a living note, not a one-time statement. If the way this
          site works changes in a meaningful way, I want this page to change
          with it.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 12, 2026.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
